## Introduction
The Note Taking App is a simple and user-friendly desktop application built using PyQt5 in Python. It allows users to create, edit, and save notes in an intuitive graphical interface. The app provides a convenient way to manage your notes efficiently.

## Features
- Create new notes with a customizable text editor.
- Edit existing notes easily using the built-in text editor.
- Save your notes as text files to your preferred location.
- Clear the contents of a note to start afresh.
- Minimalistic and easy-to-use GUI.

## Installation
1. Clone the repository to your local machine:

   ```
   git clone https://github.com/your_username/note-taking-app.git
   ```

2. Install the required dependencies:

   ```
   pip install PyQt5
   ```

## Usage
1. Run the application:

   ```
   python main.py
   ```

2. The Note Taking App window will open, providing an interface to create, edit, and save notes.

3. To create a new note, start typing in the text editor area.

4. To save the note, click the "Save" button, and choose the location to save the note as a text file.



